com.rohanclan.cfml.plugindebug
Class DebugSettings

java.lang.Object
  com.rohanclan.cfml.plugindebug.DebugSettings
public class DebugSettings
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains the boolean flags that indicate whether debugging should be enabled for any given package. Individual classes in each package should implement a field declared as: private static final boolean DEBUG = DebugSettings.{package_id_value}; Where {package_id_value} represents one of the fields in this class. If you want to show debug messages for a complete package you should change the relevant field in this class to true. If you want to only debug a specific class you can turn off debugging for the package and just turn it on for that class. See the javadocs for DebugUtils for information on the recommended way to output debug information.

Version:

Author:
